BUGS / TODO (historical list from UNINETT; many items addressed in this tree)

Addressed in current source:
- IPv6 hop limit / "TTL" on receive: IPV6_RECVHOPLIMIT + recvmsg (IPV6_HOPLIMIT cmsg); print as hops=N like IPv4 ttl=.
- Kernel timestamps (-k): SO_TIMESTAMP + recvmsg SCM_TIMESTAMP for receive-side RTT when -k is set.
- Long-run DNS failures: retry getaddrinfo every RESOLVE_RETRY_SEC (30s); main loop sleeps if no raw sockets yet.
- stdin hostname vs DNS: PING line shows user label, optional canonical name, and resolved addr.
- Duplicate replies: mod-100 dupcheck was removed (false duplicate drops / inflated loss); loss uses nsent[] vs nreceived[].
- pr_pack6: hnum bounds use >= nhosts (was > nhosts).

Still open / optional:
- Further polish of display format for resolved vs user-supplied names.
- Packed output mode could include IPv6 hop count for parity with IPv4 ttl field.
- Optional: safe duplicate detection (e.g. per-host last-sequence map without mod-100 aliasing).

See CHANGELOG.md / git history for portability work (Linux, macOS, Makefile, README).
